Following the Vice President's meetings with Arab leaders in Dubai, she directed her National Security Advisor, Dr. Phil Gordon, to travel to Israel and update Israeli officials on her meetings and continue consultations on the conflict with Hamas. Dr. Gordon met with various Israeli officials, including President Isaac Herzog and opposition leader Yair Lapid, reaffirming the Biden-Harris Administration's support for Israel's right to self-defense against Hamas. He emphasized the importance of adhering to international humanitarian law, delivering humanitarian assistance, and protecting civilians. Dr. Gordon also discussed the situation in the West Bank and expressed concern about escalating tensions and settler violence. He outlined the principles of the Biden-Harris Administration's approach to reconstruction, security, and governance in Gaza and reiterated their commitment to a two-state solution. Dr. Gordon also discussed broader regional dynamics and U.S. efforts to deter aggression and prevent escalation.